  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0da9\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0daf\u0db8 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A step by the Ministry of Public Administration to reduce the cost of paper",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government has decided to convert the 4-page form larger than the A4 size used by government officials to apply for foreign leave into a 2-page A4 size form to save a large amount of paper annually. have done",
        "This will be implemented on the advice of the Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena as the Minister of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government based on the frugality policy implemented in the public service, Ministry Secretary M.M.P.K. Mr. Mayadunne said.",
        "He mentioned that the cost of paper for that form can be saved by about 50 percent, and since the number of government employees who apply to go abroad annually is over one lakh, the government will save a considerable amount of paper and money with the new decision.",
        "All the points mentioned in the previous form are included in the new form, and it has already been forwarded to the Government Printing Department for printing."
      ],
